# Public Generics

A simple starter repository for a public-facing generic project.

## Overview

This repository serves as a placeholder for a generic open-source project. It can be used to host reusable utilities, library code, or documentation for a public package.

## Features

- Generic repository structure for public distribution
- Example project metadata and usage guidance
- Ready to customize for libraries, SDKs, or tooling

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-org/public-generics.git
   cd public-generics
   ```
2. Add your source files and documentation.
3. Update this README with project-specific information.

## Suggested Repository Structure

```text
public-generics/
├── src/             # source code for the library or project
├── examples/        # example usage and demos
├── docs/            # documentation and guides
├── tests/           # unit and integration tests
├── README           # project overview and setup instructions
└── LICENSE          # project license
```

